## Spec-Driven Development (SDD)

Plan substantial changes through structured artifacts before writing code. Backend: **<%= it.sdd.backend %>**.

**Lifecycle**

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  P[proposal] --> S[specs]
  P --> D[design]
  S --> T[tasks]
  D --> T
  T --> A[apply]
  A --> V[verify]
  V --> R[archive]
```

**Commands** (Claude: `/sdd-*`; Copilot: prompt files in `.github/prompts/`)
- `/sdd-explore <topic>` — investigate before committing.
- `/sdd-propose` → `/sdd-spec` + `/sdd-design` → `/sdd-tasks` → `/sdd-apply` → `/sdd-verify` → `/sdd-archive`.

**Artifacts** live in <% if (it.sdd.backend === "none") { %>the conversation (not persisted — enable a backend to keep them).<% } else { %>`openspec/changes/<change-name>/` and are **versioned in git** (reviewable in PRs, readable by any AI tool).<% } %>

**Rules**
- For non-trivial features, create a proposal/spec before implementing.
- Specs are the source of truth for *what*; design for *how*; tasks track progress.
- After implementing, run `/sdd-verify` against the spec, then `/sdd-archive`.
<% if (it.sdd.backend === "hybrid") { %>- Engram (if installed) augments cross-session memory; the in-repo files remain canonical.
<% } %>
